<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture,Products.Mimic" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="133" MadCap:lastWidth="510">
    <body>
        <p>You can create a blur-inside effect in conjunction with a shape that you add to<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText>. This is a useful effect, for example, if you want to hide a particular area of<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText>, perhaps information that is confidential. You can draw a shape around the area of the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText> that you want to hide and then apply the blur-inside effect, determining how much "blurriness" is used. The area inside the shape is blurred, but the rest of the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText> around the shape remains clear. You can even have multiple shapes on<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText>, each with a blur-inside effect.</p>
    </body>
</html>